### raw-writer-2 API test calls
# Configurable host:
@host = http://localhost:8080

# Timestamps must be RFC3339. Update these as needed.
@ts = 2026-04-02T10:00:00Z
@ts2 = 2026-04-02T10:01:00Z
@ts3 = 2026-04-02T10:02:00Z
@ts4 = 2026-04-02T10:03:00Z
@ts5 = 2026-04-02T10:04:00Z
@ts6 = 2026-04-02T10:05:00Z
@ts7 = 2026-04-02T10:06:00Z
@ts8 = 2026-04-02T10:07:00Z
@ts9 = 2026-04-02T10:08:00Z


# ─── Health checks ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Liveness probe (always 200 if process is up)
GET {{host}}/live

###

### Readiness probe (200 once dependencies are ready)
GET {{host}}/ready


# ─── Small payloads → stored directly in MongoDB (<5 MB) ──────────────────────

### Small JSON — compressible text type, inline body (→ Mongo, raw string)
POST {{host}}/raw-writer-test/small-json/{{ts}}
Content-Type: application/json
User-Agent: calls-http/test
X-OpenDataHub-Source: open-meteo-api
X-OpenDataHub-License: CC-BY-4.0

{"temperature_2m": 12.5, "precipitation": 0.0, "wind_speed_10m": 3.2}

###

### Small plain text — text/* is compressible but small (→ Mongo, raw string)
POST {{host}}/raw-writer-test/small-text/{{ts2}}
Content-Type: text/plain
User-Agent: calls-http/test

Hello, this is a small plain-text payload.

###

### Small binary — application/octet-stream is non-compressible, isBinary=true (→ Mongo, binary field)
# Body is 4 raw bytes (a tiny binary blob).
POST {{host}}/raw-writer-test/small-binary/{{ts3}}
Content-Type: application/octet-stream
User-Agent: calls-http/test

< ./testdata/small.bin

###

### Small BSON (valid) — JSON body with application/bson content-type; isBinary=true (→ Mongo, binary field)
# The API stores the raw bytes; the consumer interprets the JSON as BSON.
POST {{host}}/raw-writer-test/small-bson-valid/{{ts4}}
Content-Type: application/bson
User-Agent: calls-http/test

{"hello": "world", "value": 42}

###

### Small BSON (binary) — actual binary BSON bytes with application/bson content-type (→ Mongo, parsed as bson.M)
# testdata/small.bson is generated by ./testdata/generate.sh
POST {{host}}/raw-writer-test/small-bson-binary/{{ts5}}
Content-Type: application/bson
User-Agent: calls-http/test

< ./testdata/small.bson

###

### Small BSON (invalid) — malformed bytes, neither JSON nor BSON (→ Mongo, stored as raw binary)
POST {{host}}/raw-writer-test/small-bson-invalid/{{ts9}}
Content-Type: application/bson
User-Agent: calls-http/test

{hello: world, this is not valid json or bson}


# ─── Large payloads → uploaded to S3 (≥5 MB) ──────────────────────────────────
# Run ./testdata/generate.sh first to create the required files.

###

### Large JSON — compressible (→ S3 with .zst suffix, key: provider/timestamp_hash.zst)
POST {{host}}/raw-writer-test/large-json/{{ts6}}
Content-Type: application/json
User-Agent: calls-http/test
X-OpenDataHub-Source: synthetic-generator
X-OpenDataHub-Station: Bolzano-Center

< ./testdata/large.json

###

### Large binary (octet-stream) — non-compressible (→ S3 without .zst suffix, stored raw)
POST {{host}}/raw-writer-test/large-binary/{{ts7}}
Content-Type: application/octet-stream
User-Agent: calls-http/test

< ./testdata/large.bin


# ─── Validation errors → 400 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

###

### Missing User-Agent → 400 "missing header User-Agent"
POST {{host}}/raw-writer-test/missing-ua/{{ts8}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"x": 1}

###

### Invalid timestamp (not RFC3339) → 400 "invalid timestamp (RFC3339 required)"
POST {{host}}/raw-writer-test/bad-ts/20260402-100000
Content-Type: application/json
User-Agent: calls-http/test

{"x": 1}


@rawbridge=http://localhost:2000
### raw writer 2 tests
GET {{rawbridge}}/urns/urn:raw:raw-writer-test:small-text:69ce65d1958a435b2af0910f
### raw writer 2 s3 ref
GET {{rawbridge}}/urns/urn:raw:raw-writer-test:large-json:69ce65d8958a435b2af09114
